{"questionId":"22222549","questionHtml":"<p>Determine the value of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>m</mi></math> such that <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mi>g</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced></math> has only one solution for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong>EITHER</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow></mfenced></mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mi>m</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></math></p>\n<p>attempt to expand to obtain a quadratic equation&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn><mi>m</mi><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>6</mn><mi>m</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>3</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>6</mn></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>3</mn><mi>m</mi><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>6</mn><mi>m</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp;OR&nbsp; &nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>3</mn><mi>m</mi><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>6</mn><mi>m</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>recognition that discriminant&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Δ</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>&nbsp;for one solution&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mfenced><mrow><mn>6</mn><mi>m</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>OR</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow></mfenced></mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mi>m</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></math></p>\n<p>attempt to expand to obtain a quadratic equation&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn><mi>m</mi><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>6</mn><mi>m</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>3</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>6</mn></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>3</mn><mi>m</mi><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>6</mn><mi>m</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp;OR&nbsp; &nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>3</mn><mi>m</mi><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>6</mn><mi>m</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>attempt to solve their quadratic for&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math> and equating their solutions&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mfenced><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>m</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>6</mn><mi>m</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp;OR&nbsp; &nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>6</mn><mi>m</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>m</mi></mrow></mfrac><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></mfenced></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>6</mn><mi>m</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>m</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>OR</strong></p>\n<p>attempt to find <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mo>'</mo><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced></math> using the quotient rule&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mo>'</mo><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>2</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac><mfenced><mfrac><mrow><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>-</mo><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow></mfenced></mrow><msup><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup></mfrac></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mfrac><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn><msup><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow></mfrac></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp;OR&nbsp; &nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mfenced><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>6</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn><mfenced><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>6</mn></mrow></mfenced></mrow><msup><mfenced><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>6</mn></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup></mfrac></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;or equivalent&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>recognition that <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>m</mi></math>&nbsp;is the derivative of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced></math> at <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>THEN</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>⇒</mo><mi>m</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>6</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[4 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"22222549","referenceCode":"24M.1.SL.TZ2.6bii","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Determine the value of m such that fx=gx has only one solution for x.","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"ii","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 4]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 2—Functions","Topic 5 —Calculus","Topic 5 —Calculus","SL 5.6—Differentiating polynomials n E Q. Chain, product and quotient rules","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.7—Solutions of quadratic equations and inequalities, discriminant and nature of roots"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}